ZH: 他们固执己见，无法达成共识。
EN: They are each sticking to their own opinions, unable to reach a consensus.

ZH: 我们固执己见，导致了争执的发生。
EN: We insisted on our own views, leading to arguments.

ZH: 他总是固执己见，不肯听取别人的建议。
EN: He is always stubbornly sticking to his own opinions, refusing to listen to others' advice.

ZH: 她固执己见地坚持自己的信念。
EN: She stubbornly adheres to her own beliefs.

ZH: 在讨论中，他常常固执己见，不肯改变态度。
EN: In discussions, he often sticks to his own opinions and refuses to change his attitude.

ZH: 尽管别人劝说，他依然固执己见。
EN: Despite others' persuasion, he still sticks to his own opinions.

ZH: 你应该学会听取他人意见，不要总是固执己见。
EN: You should learn to listen to others' opinions and not always be stubborn.

ZH: 讨论应该是开放的，不要因为固执己见，而导致无法接受其他观点。
EN: Discussions should be open, don't be closed-minded and unable to accept other viewpoints due to stubbornness.

ZH: 学会妥协是很重要的，不要总是固执己见。
EN: It is important to learn to compromise, don't always be stubborn.

ZH: 在团队合作中，固执己见会导致矛盾和不和谐。
EN: In team collaboration, stubbornness can lead to conflicts and disharmony.

ZH: 对于这个问题，大家不应该固执己见。
EN: For this issue, everyone should not be stubborn.

ZH: 固执己见会限制个人的发展空间。
EN: Stubbornness can limit personal growth potential.

ZH: 固执己见可能导致理解误会。
EN: Stubbornness can lead to misunderstandings.

ZH: 要学会认真倾听他人的看法，不要固执己见。
EN: Learn to listen carefully to others' views, don't be stubborn.

ZH: 他一贯固执己见，不会被轻易改变。
EN: He has always been stubborn and won't be easily swayed.

ZH: 团队的成功需要团结合作，而不是固执己见。
EN: Team success requires unity and cooperation, not stubbornness.

ZH: 他们之间一直存在着固执己见的冲突。
EN: There has always been a conflict of stubbornness between them.

ZH: 学会尊重他人意见是摆脱固执己见的第一步。
EN: Learning to respect others opinions is the first step to overcoming stubbornness.

ZH: 在解决问题时，需要放下固执己见，多听取不同的意见。
EN: In problem solving, it is important to let go of stubbornness and listen to different opinions.

ZH: 工作中要灵活变通，而不是固执己见。
EN: In work, it is important to be flexible and not stubborn.
